The Herald Rumbidzayi Zinyuke Senior Reporter MUSICIAN Greatman Gwaze and his wife Silibaziso Masara have been blessed with a baby boy. Baby Karran Gwaze was born yesterday at Sally Mugabe Central Hospital in Harare. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-548685" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman2a.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman2a.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman2a-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Both mother and son are healthy and were discharged this afternoon. Greatman, who could not hide his joy, said he was a proud father and thanked God for giving him the bundle of joy. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-548686" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman3a.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman3a.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/05/greatman3a-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “My good news is that my baby boy was born yesterday at around mid day. A new star has been born, someone that I will pass the baton to, someone who will push me to become a better person. All the music I will do from now on is for him,” he said.